==English==
===Adjective===
'''haline'''
# [[salty]]; [[saline]]
# of, or relating to the degree of [[saltiness]]
===Derived terms===
*[[euryhaline]]
*[[stenohaline]]
*[[thermohaline]]

Haline is used for example as part of the compound word thermohaline, regarding temperature and salinity, which in turn is most commonly used in the phrase "thermohaline circulation" which is an ocean current caused by temperature and salinity differences between masses of water. It would be nice if "saline," "thermosaline," and "thermosaline current" were simply used instead, but only "saline" commonly is.